{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778549532,"nonce":"3t3fTQ5Es9vC9/TOPZeS4PziwRQ=","title":"Pre-go motor mask follow-up matrix (triggered from f47abb1)","message":"Triggered by `f47abb1` (lit-replication 6-cell matrix; commit `8018e57`). The two best cells on within-cell velocity RMSE — `lit__post_nojerk` (within-RMSE ≈ 0.026 m/s, hold drift 2.3 mm) and `lit__full_nojerk` (within-RMSE ≈ 0.026 m/s, hold drift 2.7 mm) — both retain a residual ~2–3 mm pre-go forward drift. This is well below the catastrophic flat-schedule cells (22–24 mm) but still above the \u003c 0.5 mm \"good hold\" target.\n\n## Hypothesis\n\nAdding the pre-go motor mask (`--nn-output-pre-go λ`, see `5acdaae` strategy 1) on top of either powerlaw + no-jerk cell will suppress the residual pre-go drift further without degrading the post-go kinematics already produced by these cells.\n\n## Proposed matrix (concrete next-step)\n\nHold the rest of `f47abb1` cell `lit__post_nojerk` (powerlaw `(t/T)^6` post-go, jerk off, `nn_hidden_derivative=1e-3`, equal hold/running weights, `p_catch=0.5`, GRU, n_replicates=5, seed=42) and sweep `--nn-output-pre-go` ∈ {0 (anchor = cell `lit__post_nojerk`), 1e-2, 1e-1, 1.0}.\n\nOptional second axis: repeat on `lit__full_nojerk` (powerlaw throughout) to check that the mask interacts the same way with the full-trial vs post-go schedule.\n\n## Decision criteria\n\n- **Primary**: hold drift (mm) — target \u003c 0.5 mm.\n- **Secondary (must not regress)**: within-cell vel RMSE (m/s) — should stay near the f47abb1 baseline of ~0.026; large increases would indicate the mask is interfering with the post-go solution. Peak forward velocity (m/s) — should remain in the 0.7–1.0 range; collapse to near-zero would indicate the mask is over-penalising controller output.\n- Report absolute within-cell RMSE per cell; do not lead with within/across ratios (see corrective comments on `f47abb1`, `c99ad9d`, `4d38c15`).\n\n## Cross-refs\n\n- `f47abb1` — triggering matrix, residual drift in the no-jerk powerlaw cells.\n- `5acdaae` — anti-anticipation menu (strategy 1: `--nn-output-pre-go`).\n- `c99ad9d` — training-methods coord (file a one-line cross-ref comment once this issue is queued).\n- `2bc95fd` — prior 6-cell anti-anticipation matrix; combo cell (motor_pre + smooth_high) was the strongest variance-collapse cell on the broken-hold baseline.\n\n## Status\n\nFiled but not yet committed to run — placeholder pending a future scheduling decision.","files":null}]}